  sodium: 1350 mg
---

In a small #pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a big
pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook
until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce. Trim and remove strings from
@snow peas{4%ounce}. Quarter @lime{1}.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all
over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high
heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked
through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan.

When rice has 5 minutes left, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken
over medium-high heat. Add snow peas and season with salt and pepper. Cook,
stirring, until just tender, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> TIP: If needed, add a splash of water to help the snow peas soften.

Stir cooked chicken, @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tablespoon}, @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%ounce},
and a squeeze of lime juice into pan with snow peas. Season with pepper.

Fluff rice with a fork and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}.

Divide rice between bowls and top with stir-fry and @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}.
Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.